  "chapter": {
    "number": 28,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Boldness of the Righteous"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The wicked flee when no one pursues,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the righteous are as bold as a lion.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A land in rebellion has many rulers,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but a man of understanding and knowledge maintains order.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A destitute leader who oppresses the poor",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "is like a driving rain that leaves no food.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Those who forsake the law praise the wicked,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but those who keep the law resist them.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Evil men do not understand justice,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but those who seek the LORD comprehend fully.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Better a poor man who walks with integrity",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "than a rich man whose ways are perverse.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A discerning son keeps the law,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but a companion of gluttons disgraces his father.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He who increases his wealth by interest and usury",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "lays it up for one who is kind to the poor.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Whoever turns his ear away from hearing the law,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "even his prayer is detestable.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He who leads the upright along the path of evil will fall into his own pit,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the blameless will inherit what is good.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A rich man is wise in his own eyes,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but a poor man with discernment sees through him.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When the righteous triumph, there is great glory,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but when the wicked rise, men hide themselves.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He who conceals his sins will not prosper,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but whoever confesses and renounces them will find mercy.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Blessed is the man who is always reverent,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4262
          },
          {
            "text": "but he who hardens his heart falls into trouble.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Like a roaring lion or a charging bear",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "is a wicked ruler over a helpless people.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A leader who lacks judgment is also a great oppressor,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but he who hates dishonest profit will prolong his days.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A man burdened by bloodguilt will flee into the Pit;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4263
          },
          {
            "text": "let no one support him.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He who walks with integrity will be kept safe,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but whoever is perverse in his ways will suddenly fall.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The one who works his land will have plenty of food,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but whoever chases fantasies will have his fill of poverty.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A faithful man will abound with blessings,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but one eager to be rich will not go unpunished.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "To show partiality is not good,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "yet a man will do wrong for a piece of bread.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A stingy man",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4264
          },
          {
            "text": "hastens after wealth",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and does not know that poverty awaits him.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He who rebukes a man will later find more favor",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "than one who flatters with his tongue.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He who robs his father or mother, saying, “It is not wrong,”",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "is a companion to the man who destroys.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A greedy man stirs up strife,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but he who trusts in the LORD will prosper.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 26,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He who trusts in himself is a fool,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but one who walks in wisdom will be safe.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 27,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Whoever gives to the poor will not be in need,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but he who hides his eyes will receive many curses.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 28,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When the wicked come to power, people hide themselves;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but when they perish, the righteous flourish.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
